	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, this is obviously an insanely nice item for any class.  The statistics are certainly a bonus and the AC is quite good, as is the 75 HP/Mana.  The real kicker is the +25 SvMagic though, with the SvPoison never hurting either and the effect being icing.  Who would benefit the most from this item?  Well, keeping in mind that everyone would want it as resist gear and for the stats, the top candidates would be the Ranger and Monk for melee characters.<br><br>Sure it weighs a little but a Monk would gain greatly from the AC and the HP, Strength and saves.  The Ranger would actually gain the most, with relatively close AC to other options and useful raises to HP/Mana, Strength and Wisdom.  And, while casters would benefit greatly overall, I really can't see a resist piece this good going in that direction, never mind the extinguish fatigue business.  Actually, ignore the effect anyways for Rogues and Warriors, they have Invigor (or Invigorate) on pieces already.  Actually all plate classes have much better AC pieces anyways, this would be situational gear for many capable of VP plundering.<br><br>I don't know how this was awarded or who it generally defaults to but it is one piece that cannot really be poorly used.  Still, many melee characters would use the Dain's crown over this on a day to day basis.  So, perhaps it does belong to a Druid or something after all.  They certainly aren't getting in on the Dain's anytime soon.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
